content.description: Pull a small roof and follow the bolts to the crack.
Approximately middle of the wall, left of the alcove still. Crack supplemented with 4 bolts. Good warm-up.
content.protection: You could get by with only 4 draws, if comfortable with the grade, otherwise supplement with a few cams up to #1 IIRC. Bolted anchor at the top, shared with the route to the left of this one.
content.location: Approximately middle of the wall, left of the alcove still.

content.description:
Nice clean face that's mostly 5.10 with a distinct 5.11a/b crux. Techy small crimps and sidepulls, balancy rather than pumpy. Well bolted, optional small cam in horizontal slot before the first bolt.

Can be TR'd from the 10b to the right.
content.protection: 5 bolts. Optional small cam before the first bolt. Mussey hooks.
content.location: Left of center of the Main wall. Clean face with a distinct broken vertical seam.

content.description: Rather dirty corner between Freaky-Styly and Cosmic Spillway. All gear, use Freaky Styly anchor for lower off or TR. Nothing exceptional about the climb, with more use it would surely clean up a bit and then it would be fun to do.
content.location: Corner between Freaky-Styly and Cosmic Spillway

content.description: Good variety on well bolted route on the right side of the central area. Start on the bolted face, then you get a break on a big ledge before steep upper part which has plentiful holds as long as you look around...
content.protection: 6 or so bolts, maybe a small cam for right after the big ledge but not really necessary.
content.location: Right side of the central area.

content.description: Bolted line on the right side of the central Green cliff on distinctly black rock. Nice variety of big moves between mostly big holds, with a few jams interspered. Quite physical.
content.protection: 5 or 6 bolts. Hooks at the top
content.location: Bolted line on the right side of the central Green cliff on distinctly black rock.

content.description: Great warm-up for other climbs on the wall, with cool movement.
content.protection: 9 draws plus bolted anchor at the top
content.location: Located on left side of the Green Cliff, perpendicular to the main wall.

content.description: Climbs a small roof in the middle of the wall. Very good warm-up.
content.location: Alcove in the middle of the wall, route climbs over the roof.

content.description: Awesome sport climb with two distinct cruxes and engaging climbing in-between.
content.protection: 10 bolts. Anchors at the top. Very well protected.
content.location: First bolted route on the main wall, right off Necromancer corner
